Czech Coalition Party Mulls Higher Corporate Tax, Pravo Reports

-- B y   P e t e r   L a c a
-- 
2011-03-23T07:07:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-23/czech-coalition-party-mulls-higher-corporate-tax-pravo-reports.html
Public Affairs, the smallest Czech
ruling-coalition party, may propose an increase in the corporate
 tax rate  to 21 percent or 22 percent, from the current 19
percent,  Pravo  reported, citing a lawmaker for the party.  Michal Babak of Public Affairs said the party also wants to
raise the income tax for people making more than four times the
average wage per month, the newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Peter Laca in Prague at 
 placa@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Willy Morris at 
 wmorris@bloomberg.net  